      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The argument that strict enforcement is \"inhumane\" ignores the reality of the rule of law; a system without boundaries is chaos, and chaos is inherently inhumane. Compassion demands order, and enforcing laws provides a predictable, safe structure for everyone within the nation. Furthermore, allowing unchecked entry creates dangerous conditions—like exploitation and human trafficking—which strict enforcement is designed to prevent, ultimately protecting vulnerable people more effectively than open borders.",
      "source": "target",
